reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 29, 2022
reviews.reviewText: The color is gorgeous! Anyone saying its particle board its not Its an engineered wood. Pay attention to the instructions. I put one shelf on backwards and had to start over. LOL. I have a 27" TV on mine now in the guest bedroom and it looks aweome! I didnt want something to expensive and this fit my needs and my budget. I am VERY happy with my purchase!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 12, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Served it's purpose
reviews.reviewText: This cabinet wasn't as sturdy as I had hoped. It was fairly easy to assemble, however, there was one piece missing. It was the magnetic strip that goes on the top corner of the doors. At that point in the assembly, it was not worth taking it apart to return it. It is very frustrating to have a part missing, however, I am glad it wasn't an important part. I will just have to buy some magnets to glue on myself. The back wall of the cabinet was thin cardboard with a coating to match the "wood-looking boards". Overall, it was overpriced for what the end product turned out to be.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 6, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars get what you pay for.
reviews.reviewText: I had a space with very specific dimentions.dimensions. Finally found this piece and I liked the color.However, this was a pain in the rear to put together. Some of the pilot holes were shallow, and a lot of them chipped and shattered the surface when I put the screws in. I had used a manual screw driver to try and avoid this. Instead of one cardboard back piece, for some reason this comes with 2 and a black plastic middle peice to join them. This piece was about an inch longer than the backs and made the wood top impossible to install. Had to grind it down in order to finish assembly. Good thing it came with extra hardware, because one of their screws was malformed and unusable.Even going back and tightening everything down, this is still a bit wobbly. For my use, in the laundry room for a bit more storage, it's acceptable. I wouldn't plan to move this piece around, though!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 20, 2022
reviews.reviewText: When I got this and took the pieces out of the clearly UNdamaged box I was disappointed to see a large crack in the left front side of the frame as well as the right door handle is split and cracked...
